text: The Gracile frilled tree frog (Kurixalus gracilloides) is a frog. It lives Vietnam. People have seen it more than 150 meters above sea level. The adult male frog is 27.9â€“31.2 mm long from nose to rear end. The skin of the frog's back is gold-brown in color with dark marks on the back. There is some fringed skin on its legs. There is some webbed skin on the front feet and more on the back feet. ==References== Category:Frogs of Asia
